string-array.name: message_of_a_khmer_rouge_survivor
string-array.item: \“Don\'t forget us. And don\'t let it happen again — to anyone.\”

\“They tried to erase us. But I remembered the names. I remembered the taste of my mother\'s soup. I remembered the stories my sister whispered when we were scared. I remembered how to grow food when there was none.\”
\“Even when we had nothing, we had each other. And if you still have someone, hold them close. Feed them. Forgive them. Teach them.\”
\“Build a world where no child has to survive like we did. A world where kindness is not a weakness, but the only power worth having.\”

string-array.name: bug_catcher_dialogue_array
string-array.item: I\'m only in this to catch a land eel!
Does anyone see my bug catching net?
Call me the BEAST MASTER!
Will there be pie?
There\'s an aroma wafting off our leader...

resources.string: Congratulations! You beat our 5 contest trainers! You just earned a fabulous prize! [Player] received a NUGGET! By the way, would you like to join TEAM ROCKET? We\'re a group dedicated to evil using POKEMON! Want to join? Are you sure? Come on, join us! I\'m telling you to join! OK, you need convincing! I\'ll make you an offer you can\'t refuse! With your ability, you could become a top leader in TEAM ROCKET!

Hello there! Welcome to the world of JAVA! My name is FOO BAR! People call me the JAVA PROF! This world is inhabited by creatures called OBJECT! For some people, OBJECT are pets. Others use them for fights. Myself... I study OBJECT as a profession. First, what is your name?
This is my grandson. He\'s been your rival since you were a baby. ...Erm, what is his name again?
That\'s right! I remember now! His name is %s!
Your very own JAVA legend is about to unfold! A world of dreams and adventure with OBJECT awaits! Let\'s go!

string-array.name: seed_shop_dialogue_array
string-array.item: Hello! I was cleaning out my father\'s belongings when I found these mystery seeds. I can\'t keep a cactus alive. You have a green thumb, how about you grow these seeds for me? If you get me 3 mystery products, I\'ll give you some coins! Also, you can keep the shovel, watering can, and mystery seeds!
Hello! Please germinate and grow the mystery seeds, then harvest 3 mystery products and place them in the shipping bin.
Hello! The mystery products you\'ve harvested were FAR out. Like OUTER-SPACE far. You can probably bring about world peace with what you\'re growing.

string-array.name: clippit_dialogue_array
string-array.item: It looks like you\'re trying to bring about world peace. Would you like some help?
We\'re going to get the entire world stoned for a week! We\'ll need a lot of mystery product. Start by tilling 4,200 GrowableTile.
Tilling 4,200 GrowableTile with a shovel will take all day. Fortunately, there\'s a rust-bucket robot that is software-upgradeable. It\'s time to work smarter (not harder)!

We\'re the first to finish, but now we have to wait for everyone else. Instead of wasting time doing nothing, how about we learn the basics of modifying genes? Then we can splice the gene responsible for THC production into the genome of the world\'s fastest growing organism.

Alright! You\'ve created THC-producing-kelp, and you\'re one step closer to getting the entire world stoned for a week. Let\'s go on a side quest to deposit the mystery seeds into the world\'s seed bank.
You\'ve been recruited to a team who are on a mission to terraform the moon. It\'s time to create some moonrocks!
This is it, the final run. The Panthers are wrecking havoc and keeping law enforcement busy. You got Molly in your ears with Mary as your tracer. Welcome to Straylight.

string-array.name: messages_dialogue_array_run_four
string-array.item: So a List is basically like a basket. You can put multiple things inside instead of just one. I like that metaphor.
Okay... but how do you actually make one in Java?
You declare it. Like: List groceries = new ArrayList(); That makes an empty basket ready to hold grocery items.
Empty basket = sad basket. Fill it with pizza already!
And then .add() puts stuff inside, right? So if I add \"Apples,\" \"Bananas,\" and \"Milk,\" now my List has 3 things.
Exactly. And each item has an index. The first one you added is at index 0.
0?? Not 1?? Bruh. So groceries.get(0) is apples?? That\'s sus.
Yeah, I keep wanting to start at 1. That\'s gonna mess me up.
It\'s a programming standard. Just takes practice. But yeah, groceries.get(0) will print \"Apples.\"
Cool, I’ll just .get() \"Cookies\" instead.
What about checking the size? That was .size(), right?
Yep! That tells you how many items are in the List. Super useful for looping through.
For loop = \"go through all the snacks one by one\" lol.
And .remove() kicks something out of the basket, .set() swaps it with something else?
Right. Remove takes it out completely, set replaces it.
So I can remove broccoli and replace with fries. Done.
***COLLECTING LEARNER\'S NOTES***

string-array.name: messages_dialogue_array_run_three
string-array.item: Okay, so for loops are about repeating stuff without copy-pasting lines of code. Super efficient.
Wait... so like, instead of writing waterPlant() five times, you use a loop?
Lol just write it 5 times... faster.
But the loop has 3 parts, right? Start, stop, update? I think I get start (i = 0) and update (i++), but the stop part confuses me.
The stop condition is how long it keeps looping. Like i < 5. If you change that number, it changes how many times it runs.
Bro I\'d set it to i < 9999 and water plants forever.
Ohhh. So if you use plants.size() instead of 5, it automatically knows how many plants are in the list. That makes sense.
Yep. That\'s dynamic. Doesn\'t matter if it\'s 3 plants or 300k.
300,000 plants?? nah fam I\'m done after 2.
And then there\'s a \"for-each loop\"? I kinda missed that part.
Looks like magic. One line to rule them all. Lord of the Plants!
LOL. And break means stop early... continue means skip the rest of that one plant?
Correct. Break exits the loop, continue just skips one round.
So basically: break when I\'m tired, continue when it\'s broccoli. Got it.
Haha. Okay, I think I get it now: (1) Use loops for repetition. (2) Counter loop vs. for-each. (3) Break = stop, Continue = skip.
Yep, that\'s the roadmap.
***COLLECTING LEARNER\'S NOTES***

string-array.name: messages_dialogue_array_run_two
string-array.item: So... when I inspect the plant, how does the robot decide if it waters or not?
That\'s the if\/else part. If the plant is dry -> water. Else -> skip to the next one.
Skip? Nah, I just drown all of mine. Easy win.
But like... in the code, where does that choice go?
ELSE\: order pizza. Done.
Ohhh. So [if] checks the condition, and [else] is what happens when it\'s false?
Exactly. The robot always does one or the other - never both.
Unless you code it wrong. Then it does nothing. Like me.
Okay, I think I get it now. If dry -> water. Else -> skip. Simple pattern.
Yes. That\'s the whole logic.

string-array.name: messages_dialogue_array_run_one
string-array.item: Okay so... the blueprint thing kind of made sense, but I still don\'t get how a class is not the actual object. It feels weird that something made of text becomes... a thing.
Think of it like the recipe vs. the cake. The recipe isn\'t edible. The cake is the object. Java classes are recipes. When Java \"makes\" an object, that\'s the cake.
My recipe is for \"NotBadNotBadCake\". Ingredients: sugar, flour, and pure swagger.
Field vs. method is still confusing me. I keep mixing them up.
Fields = facts. Methods = actions.
Field: coolnessLevel = 9000. Method: showOff().
And comments... why write stuff that Java ignores? That part confused me too.
Because they\'re notes for humans, not computers. Think of them like sticky notes on your code so future-you doesn\'t forget what you were doing.
My only comment will be: \'\/\/ I have no idea what I\'m doing, but it worked once\'.
Okay... I think I\'m getting it. Class = blueprint, fields = things it knows, methods = things it can do. And objects = the real thing we use.
That\'s it. You\'ve basically got everything!
I learned that chickens have methods. My chicken method is crossRoad(). That\'s all it does. It just crosses roads... forever.
